:0:"";}i:10;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"menu location";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:11;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"responsive";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:12;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"skyScape theme";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:13;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:21:"Smart Responsive Menu";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:14;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:20:"xScape Menu Designer";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:33:"http://www.dev4press.com/?p=19762";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:263:"New major release for xScape Theme Framework brings very important new features, updates and core improvements. Several areas are completely rewritten to allow future expanding (menus, grid system, Google Web Fonts module) with upcoming responsive themes in mind.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"MillaN";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5341:"<p>New major release for xScape Theme Framework brings very important new features, updates and core improvements. Several areas are completely rewritten to allow future expanding (menus, grid system, Google Web Fonts module) with upcoming responsive themes in mind.</p>\n<div class="xss-infobox xss-infobox-color-red"><strong>Upgrade Information:</strong>New framework requires WordPress 3.2 or newer to work. Themes using the framework must be updated after you switch to new xScape Core 1.9. Make sure you backup your theme before proceeding.</div>\n<h4>Expanded Grids Implementation</h4>\n<p>So far, all themes were using Blueprint CSS Framework. But, this framework was limiting, and for future themes that are all planned as responsive it is not usable. So, framework now supports use of different grid frameworks.</p>\n<p>Upcoming skyScape theme is fully responsive theme, and it will use brand new CSS Framework developed for this purpose. All existing theme will continue using Blueprint CSS Framework, since there is no way to make grid model interchangeable.</p>\n<div id="attachment_19803" class="wp-caption alignright" style="width: 248px"><a title="Menu Settings Panel" href="http://cdn.dev4press.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/xscape_typical_menu_settings.png" rel="lightbox"><img class="wp-image-19803" title="Menu Settings Panel" alt="Menu Settings Panel" src="http://cdn.dev4press.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/xscape_typical_menu_settings-297x300.png" width="238" height="240" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Menu Settings Panel</p></div>\n<h4>Rewritten Menus Implementation</h4>\n<p>The area that got most changes in 1.9 are menus. First thing you will notice is that all settings related to menus are gone from main theme Settings panel into own, new Menu Settings panel. Here you will see one tab for each menu location supported by the theme (2 or 3 in all current themes). Each menu has two main groups of settings: Content and CSS Styles (image on the right). If theme supports additional menus (like Smart Responsive Menu), settings for those menus (if they have them) will be listed for each menu location that supports them.</p>\n<p>Major new change for menus is that if you design them with xScape Menu Designer, these menus will support icons for menu items. Icons are implemented as font icons, and Font Awesome is built into the framework.</p>\n<h4>Old Themes and New</h4>\n<p>All these changes mean, that in the future, different menu implementation can be added to the themes. Current theme <strong>lightScape</strong> will get support for <a href="http://d4p.me/ccsrm" target="_blank">Smart Responsive Menu</a> (it would require too many changes to implement). Other existing themes will remain the same. All future themes will be responsive, and will not use old Superfish menus, they will all rely on Smart Responsive Menu only.</p>\n<p>All existing themes are already released. But, you will not be able to update until you update xScape Core to version 1.9. Updater will not offer themes updates without xScape Core 1.9. Changes in the themes require new framework, and themes will not work anymore with older framework versions. New versions have updated translation files and fixes for some styling and layout issues.</p>\n<h4>Module: Google Web Fonts 2.0</h4>\n<p>New version of this module now includes 640 fonts. But, since Google is expanding this list very often, this module can now get the up to date list on it&#8217;s own. To do this, you must provide valid <a href="https://code.google.com/apis/console/" target="_blank">Google Developer API key</a>. Module has new options for control of fonts adding, and also new way for loading fonts without style including.</p>\n<h4>Module: ShareThis 1.6</h4>\n<p>Module is expanded with Zocial Icons set. These are font based icons, and you can specify font size for the icons, instead of selecting predefined image set style. Plan for future updates is to rewrite this module with more options and cleanup of icons sets and supported services.</p>\n<h4>Module: SideScroller 1.2</h4>\n<p>New Edit post button is added (disabled by default). Through use of filter (so only theme can enable it if needed), it can use Font Awesome icons.</p>\n<h4>Other Framework Changes</h4>\n<p>xScape Theme Framework 1.9 and xScape Core 1.9 <strong>now require WordPress 3.2</strong> or newer to work. JavaScript and CSS loading is improved and organization of these files changed, so more files are moved to the Core. jQueryUI, Colorbox, Modernizr and Superfish scripts are updated. PNGFix file loading is also removed. Framework loads own shared JavaScript file, and most of that JS is gone from individual themes. Stying for some of the admin panels improved. There are many under-the-hood changes to improve loading, working with settings and meta elements, templates&#8230;</p>\n<p>So, the new framework version is a big improvement over the old one, and it will allow further expanding and better themes in the future that will be, as already announced, HTML5 and responsive only. If you notice any issues with the framework or themes, please let me know through support forums.</p>\n<script src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~s/adsense@gdragon.info?i=http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/themes-news/xscape-framework-and-core-1-9/" type="text/javascript" charset="utf-8"></script>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:82:"http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/themes-news/xscape-framework-and-core-1-9/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"5";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:69:"\n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n\n \n \n \n \n \n ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:21:"Dev4Press Updater 2.2";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"http://www.dev4press.com/20