;a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"MillaN";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1527:"<p>xScape Theme Framework plans have changed a bit, and the roadmap is updated. Previous plan for major 1.9 release are now moved for 2.0 version (later this year), and now 1.9 will get some very important features related to menus and it drops support for WordPress 3.0/3.1.</p>\n<p>With new theme coming soon (skyScape is in work now, and it should be released with xScape 1.9 now), problem was to add new rendering for menu that would be responsive, and still have old menu rendering methods. So, the menu subsystem in the xScape will be completely overhauled to support different rendering engines, and that rendering engines for menus can be registered by plugins or individual themes. New menu for xScape will be added to handle settings that are related to menus.</p>\n<p>Changes will be made to grid system used for rendering, so that themes can work with responsive grids also.</p>\n<p>Also, due to increasing number of problems caused by jQuery/jQueryUI added with latest versions of WordPress, new version will be using jQueryUI 1.9, and it will be dropping support for WordPress 3.0 / 3.1 (uses old jQuery, that is not supported by new jQueryUI).</p>\n<p>So, there are very exiting changes coming to xScape, and with new theme to be released soon also, you can be sure that xScape Framework future looks bright.</p>\n<script src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~s/adsense@gdragon.info?i=http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/development/coming-soon-xscape-theme-framework-1-9/" type="text/javascript" charset="utf-8"></script>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:91:"http://www.dev4press.com/2013/blog/de