se_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:264:"New major version for GD bbPress Toolbox Pro is released bringing many updates to handling of BBCodes (filters for advanced control), many new and updated BBCodes (inlcuding email, anchor, iframe...), new enhanced options, updates to styling and several bug fixes.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"MillaN";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1117:"<p>New GD bbPress Toolbox Pro 1.4 brings several bugs fixed, libraries updated, improvements and few new things for compatibility with recently released bbPress 2.2 (now bbPress 2.2.3) including support for dynamic roles (used instead of the default WordPress assigned ones).</p>\n<p>Dynamic roles are added to replace default roles in WordPress and to help sort out problems with capabilities. So, GD bbPress Toolbox will now show only dynamic roles in all its settings if you upgrade to bbPress 2.2.x, users of older bbPress version will still see all roles. Toolbar menu options are expanded with links to new bbPress tools pages.</p>\n<p>If you have any issues with the plugin, please report them in the forum.<div class="xss-infobox xss-infobox-color-green"><h3>Official Website</h3>\n<p>GD bbPress Toolbox Pro has own website:</p>\n<p>Home: <a href="http://www.gdbbpbox.com/" target="_blank">www.gdbbpbox.com</a></div></p>\n<script src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~s/adsense@gdragon.info?i=http://www.dev4press.com/2012/blog/plugins-news/gd-bbpress-toolbox-pro-1-4/" type="text/javascript" charset="utf-8"></script>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/Co