;s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:291:"After a week of testing and fine tuning, first stable release for first GD CPT Tools Pro module is here. Index 1.0 has a complete set of features I have planned initially for it (with few more ideas still on paper). It is easy to configure and it can be set to work with (almost) all themes.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"MillaN";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2017:"<p>After a week of testing and fine tuning, first stable release for first GD CPT Tools Pro module is here. Index 1.0 has a complete set of features I have planned initially for it (with few more ideas still on paper). It is easy to configure and it can be set to work with (almost) all themes.</p>\n<p>Module can work with any post type, even the post type that has no archives (rewrite rules for archives), since you can specify the slug to use in the URL for each post type. To display index with terms, you can use function (in documentation for the module), or widget called Indexer. Process of indexing is done in the background (for initial indexing), or each time published post is saved for post types that you enabled Index.</p>\n<blockquote><p><strong>Important</strong>: Module is available for free to all users with valid Developer or Enterprise licenses for GD Custom Posts and Taxonomies Tools Pro plugin or Dev4Press Plugins Pack. If you have Personal or Standard license for plugin or pack, you have to purchase this module. Module license is tied to plugin or pack license, and will remain valid for as long as the plugin or pack license is valid. You can&#8217;t download module or get support for it without plugin or pack license.</p></blockquote>\n<p>Module is in use on Dev4Press (in Documentation right now), and that will be expanded further soon. Also, Documentation is added for functions and filters needed for public index rendering. Tutorials for the module are already published.</p>\n<p>If you have noticed any issue with the module, please report them in the forums. If you want to try the module in action, you can request demo website. And if you decide to buy it, start from <a title="Index" href="http://www.dev4press.com/modules/gd-taxonomies-tools/index/">module home page</a>.</p>\n<script src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~s/adsense@gdragon.info?i=http://www.dev4press.com/2012/blog/modules-news/gd-cpt-tools-pro-module-index-1-0/" type="text/javascript" charset="utf-8"></script>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:87:"http://www.dev4press.com/2012/blog/modules-news/gd-cpt-tools-pro-module-index-1-0/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:42;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:66:"\n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n\n \n \n \n \n \n ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Using Index module: Walkthrough";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:85:"http://www.dev4press.com/2012/tutorials/modules/index/using-index-module-walkthrough/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explici